# ESPHome flashing

Use the **pyenv 3.11.4** install only. Do not create project venvs, install ESPHome via pip into other Python versions, or use `~/.local/bin/esphome` (3.10 / 2025.7.5 — missing `band_mode`).

```bash
ESPHOME="$HOME/.pyenv/versions/3.11.4/bin/esphome"
cd docs/examples

# USB or OTA (pass gate IP for OTA)
$ESPHOME -s gate_id <id> run gate.yaml --device <ip-or-port> --no-logs

# Or helper script (uses whatever `esphome` is on PATH — prefer explicit path above)
./flash-gate.sh <id>
```

- `gate_id` is the suffix only: `1`, `2`, `6`, `start`, `finish` → `gate-<id>` via substitution.
- Discover gates on LAN: GateStage `POST /api/gates/discover` or mDNS `_esphomelib._tcp`.
- `gate.yaml` requires ESPHome **2026.x** for `band_mode: 5GHZ` (pyenv 3.11.4 has 2026.6.2).
